    <h1>bit.ly</h1><div id="preamble">
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>System » Client » Settings » Services » bit.ly</strong></p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="_general_information">1. General information</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The online service <strong>bit.ly</strong> gives you the possibility of shortening long URLs on its website. If you saved a valid configuration for the URL shortening service, bit.ly, then the URLs that plentymarkets automatically generates for tweets on <strong><a href="/en/omni-channel/online-store/extras/twitter">Twitter</a></strong> (chapter 4) will be directly shortened.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="_registration">2. Registration</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If you don’t have a bit.ly account yet, then go to the website and <a href="https://bitly.com/a/sign_in" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>sign up</strong></a>.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="_configuration">3. Configuration</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Proceed as follows to set up bit.ly in plentymarkets.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Setting up bit.ly:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » Client » Settings » Services » bit.ly</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter your user name under <strong>Login</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter the API key that you received from bit.ly under <strong>API key</strong>.<br>
→ If you are logged into bit.ly, then you will find the API key <a href="http://bit.ly/a/your_api_key" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>here</strong>.</a></p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>save icon</strong> to save the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
